$value['web_content_4']
<div>Driving through Eastern Washington's farmland, I noticed something troubling – lots of water being used, but much of it not reaching the plants. This sparked my interest in efficient irrigation systems.</div><div><br></div><div>My research revealed that drip irrigation achieves over 90% efficiency compared to conventional sprinklers at just 60-70%. In Washington, 80% of farms use sprinklers, 15% rely on gravity and rainfall, and only 5% use drip irrigation. The switch to drip systems saves costs, increases water efficiency, and makes farming more reliable.</div><div><br></div><div>We're developing technology to collect atmospheric water for drip irrigation and creating affordable farming solutions. Through outreach with companies, farms, and our community, we're building a movement to ensure our farmers are environmentally and technologically sustainable.</div>
